benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Add custom fields to invoice item

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC10, @TC12, @TC14, @TC15, @TC18, @TC19, @TC20, @TC21, @TC24, @TC25 cover successful creation with valid data and headers.
Invalid Payload: @TC08 covers malformed request body, @TC09 covers missing request body.
Non-Existent Invoice Item: @TC05, @TC23 cover non-existent invoice item IDs.
Invalid ID Format: @TC06 covers invalid UUID format.
Missing Headers: @TC07 covers missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header.
Empty Array: @TC10 covers empty request body.
Extra Parameters: @TC11 discusses handling unknown parameters.
Large Payloads: @TC14, @TC24 cover maximum data size and system load.
Response Time & Concurrency: @TC15, @TC16 cover performance and concurrent requests.
Duplicate Custom Fields: @TC17 addresses duplicate field names.
Edge Cases: @TC19, @TC20, @TC21 cover length, special characters, injection attempts.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets requiring pagination.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests to test rate limiting or throttling.
Detailed concurrency conflict handling: No specific tests for conflicts during concurrent modifications.
Specific validation for field values (e.g., length, format): Not explicitly tested beyond basic validation.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination to verify handling of large datasets.
Include scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation.
Implement rate limiting tests to ensure system stability under load.
Create detailed concurrency conflict tests to handle race conditions.
Add validation tests for field value formats, lengths, and special characters beyond basic validation.
